1
00:01:30,800 --> 00:01:34,520
=Lady Liberty=

2
00:01:35,020 --> 00:01:37,940
=Episode 22=

3
00:02:02,300 --> 00:02:03,222
(Parting with Yan Dan at Yishui)

4
00:02:03,244 --> 00:02:06,420
(Chapter 51: Such is Fate)

5
00:02:06,420 --> 00:02:07,500
(Dingqi Reading Platform)

6
00:02:07,500 --> 00:02:10,820
(Qin Han, the Yan bounty assassin,
awakens from his crushing defeat.)

7
00:02:14,860 --> 00:02:18,820
(Chapter 51: Such is Fate)

8
00:02:37,220 --> 00:02:40,380
(Dingqi Reading Platform Real-time Data)

9
00:02:47,080 --> 00:02:48,160
Let's celebrate.

10
00:02:48,160 --> 00:02:49,520
To our new author, Sansan.

11
00:02:56,200 --> 00:02:57,280
If Lin Zhanqiao

12
00:02:58,280 --> 00:03:00,360
knew you were Sansan,

13
00:03:00,920 --> 00:03:01,480
what then?

14
00:03:04,440 --> 00:03:05,200
I don't know.

15
00:03:06,688 --> 00:03:08,120
But she'll find out eventually.

16
00:03:09,480 --> 00:03:10,280
So,

17
00:03:11,920 --> 00:03:13,600
does Zhao Lanxin

18
00:03:13,600 --> 00:03:15,400
treat you better

19
00:03:17,040 --> 00:03:18,160
than Lin Zhanqiao

20
00:03:18,480 --> 00:03:19,640
in the partnership?

21
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:25,480
That's why I wish

22
00:03:26,480 --> 00:03:27,520
Lin Zhanqiao would

23
00:03:27,520 --> 00:03:29,200
treat me like Zhao Lanxin does.

24
00:03:39,520 --> 00:03:41,080
So you still prefer Lin Zhanqiao.

25
00:03:52,520 --> 00:03:54,080
Er Jiu asked me today.

26
00:03:58,960 --> 00:03:59,920
He asked if I'd consider

27
00:04:01,911 --> 00:04:02,888
marrying him.

28
00:04:11,920 --> 00:04:13,240
Makes sense, I guess.

29
00:04:14,920 --> 00:04:15,960
If you aren't

30
00:04:16,560 --> 00:04:17,680
going to marry me,

31
00:04:17,920 --> 00:04:19,880
I might as well marry Er Jiu.

32
00:04:20,840 --> 00:04:21,680
It's not like I'm

33
00:04:22,400 --> 00:04:25,000
a successful woman like Lin Zhanqiao.

34
00:04:28,400 --> 00:04:29,000
I must

35
00:04:31,200 --> 00:04:32,120
find someone while I'm

36
00:04:33,080 --> 00:04:33,640
still young.

37
00:04:38,040 --> 00:04:39,000
They want someone

38
00:04:41,320 --> 00:04:42,240
they truly like.

39
00:04:45,880 --> 00:04:47,880
They won't marry
unless they're madly in love.

40
00:04:49,640 --> 00:04:51,560
We just need someone we don't hate.

41
00:05:11,680 --> 00:05:12,720
I like you.

42
00:05:17,440 --> 00:05:18,800
But I don't hate Er Jiu.

43
00:05:23,600 --> 00:05:25,640
Er Jiu says
his feelings for me are genuine.

44
00:05:37,560 --> 00:05:38,400
Haven't you already

45
00:05:39,280 --> 00:05:40,320
made your choice?

46
00:06:06,500 --> 00:06:11,900
(Esports Cafe Arcade)

47
00:06:15,020 --> 00:06:19,300
(Chapter 51: Such is Fate.
Parting with Yan Dan at Yishui, Sansan)

48
00:06:19,300 --> 00:06:20,260
(To have his life dictated by others...)

49
00:06:32,360 --> 00:06:32,840
Mei.

50
00:06:35,160 --> 00:06:37,040
Did you just get back from Jiangxi?

51
00:06:37,844 --> 00:06:39,040
Got back this afternoon.

52
00:06:39,080 --> 00:06:40,244
I dropped by my place first.

53
00:06:41,560 --> 00:06:42,480
Did you see Lawyer Bei?

54
00:06:43,440 --> 00:06:44,160
Problem solved?

55
00:06:46,600 --> 00:06:47,920
He's making up the difference.

56
00:06:48,044 --> 00:06:49,720
And I don't have to deal with the rest.

57
00:06:50,080 --> 00:06:51,680
That's pretty stand-up of him.

58
00:06:52,000 --> 00:06:54,000
Weren't you worried
he'd skip out on the debt

59
00:06:54,000 --> 00:06:55,880
and leave to hide from you?

60
00:06:58,160 --> 00:06:59,080
He didn't lie to me

61
00:06:59,880 --> 00:07:00,640
or use me.

62
00:07:01,200 --> 00:07:02,280
He took responsibility.

63
00:07:02,280 --> 00:07:03,120
He just did

64
00:07:03,120 --> 00:07:04,240
what he was supposed to do.

65
00:07:05,680 --> 00:07:07,560
If he had thrown you under the bus

66
00:07:07,600 --> 00:07:08,400
to take the blame,

67
00:07:08,680 --> 00:07:10,640
that would just mean
he's a terrible person

68
00:07:11,240 --> 00:07:12,120
with character flaws.

69
00:07:13,533 --> 00:07:14,800
Well, what he's doing now

70
00:07:14,800 --> 00:07:16,040
doesn't make him noble,

71
00:07:16,040 --> 00:07:16,880
nor is it love.

72
00:07:17,720 --> 00:07:18,880
Let's not lower the bar here.

73
00:07:23,160 --> 00:07:24,560
Mrs. Bei found out.

74
00:07:25,880 --> 00:07:27,160
She demanded that

75
00:07:28,440 --> 00:07:29,800
I sever all ties with Lawyer Bei.

76
00:07:31,400 --> 00:07:32,280
She's that calm

77
00:07:33,240 --> 00:07:33,920
and forgiving?

78
00:07:39,760 --> 00:07:41,560
I've only met her once,

79
00:07:42,880 --> 00:07:43,880
but I get the feeling

80
00:07:45,240 --> 00:07:46,240
she's not that simple.

81
00:07:48,400 --> 00:07:49,480
Unless she was prepared.

82
00:08:03,444 --> 00:08:04,155
Sparkling water.

83
00:08:04,200 --> 00:08:04,590
Here.

84
00:08:04,600 --> 00:08:05,000
Thank you.

85
00:08:05,880 --> 00:08:06,320
Mrs. Bei.

86
00:08:07,622 --> 00:08:08,577
Sorry, I'm late.

87
00:08:13,040 --> 00:08:13,400
Well?

88
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:15,400
Did you bring what I asked for?

89
00:08:16,560 --> 00:08:16,920
No.

90
00:08:20,466 --> 00:08:21,920
You just refuse to give it to me.

91
00:08:26,688 --> 00:08:27,640
I believe this matter

92
00:08:27,640 --> 00:08:28,760
ends here.

93
00:08:29,200 --> 00:08:30,040
Ends here?

94
00:08:35,822 --> 00:08:36,844
It's six million yuan.

95
00:08:37,240 --> 00:08:38,120
Just like that?

96
00:08:38,422 --> 00:08:39,640
After what I've sacrificed,

97
00:08:41,480 --> 00:08:42,360
it just ends here?

98
00:08:43,920 --> 00:08:45,920
This actually
has nothing to do with Zhou Mei.

99
00:08:46,480 --> 00:08:48,720
Mr. Bei needed someone
to be his corporate proxy.

100
00:08:49,066 --> 00:08:51,000
If not Zhou Mei,
it would've been someone else.

101
00:08:51,120 --> 00:08:53,280
But right now,
it is Zhou Mei, not someone else.

102
00:08:54,920 --> 00:08:56,240
Lawyer Bei's biggest mistake was

103
00:08:57,880 --> 00:08:59,320
choosing such a beautiful woman

104
00:08:59,320 --> 00:09:00,320
to act as his proxy.

105
00:09:02,240 --> 00:09:02,640
Right?

106
00:09:05,440 --> 00:09:05,880
Yes.

107
00:09:07,360 --> 00:09:08,440
My girlfriend is beautiful.

108
00:09:09,600 --> 00:09:10,960
But because she is my girlfriend,

109
00:09:11,840 --> 00:09:13,080
I can't let baseless accusations

110
00:09:13,080 --> 00:09:13,920
be pinned on her.

111
00:09:14,520 --> 00:09:15,400
I am a lawyer.

112
00:09:15,880 --> 00:09:17,440
I know how easily things can escalate.

113
00:09:20,120 --> 00:09:20,960
Are you serious?

114
00:09:23,040 --> 00:09:24,160
Is Zhou Mei your girlfriend,

115
00:09:24,760 --> 00:09:25,320
or...

116
00:09:27,240 --> 00:09:28,640
Or is she Lawyer Bei's girlfriend?

117
00:09:29,480 --> 00:09:30,640
Mrs. Bei, I'm serious.

118
00:09:30,777 --> 00:09:31,720
She is my girlfriend.

119
00:09:36,360 --> 00:09:36,680
Fine.

120
00:09:38,133 --> 00:09:39,800
I just wanted to teach her a lesson.

121
00:09:40,360 --> 00:09:41,920
I wouldn't actually send her to prison.

122
00:09:42,244 --> 00:09:44,040
In my eyes,
Zhou Mei didn't break any rules.

123
00:09:44,320 --> 00:09:46,280
If you think she played by the rules,

124
00:09:46,960 --> 00:09:47,920
I'll be the judge of

125
00:09:48,222 --> 00:09:49,600
whether she crossed the line.

126
00:09:51,240 --> 00:09:52,920
It was Mr. Bei who crossed the line.

127
00:09:57,480 --> 00:09:57,800
True.

128
00:09:59,200 --> 00:10:00,440
His biggest violation

129
00:10:01,640 --> 00:10:03,120
was getting involved with Zhou Mei.

130
00:10:06,160 --> 00:10:06,440
Fine.

131
00:10:07,320 --> 00:10:08,440
You take your Zhou Mei.

132
00:10:08,760 --> 00:10:09,800
And I'll manage my husband.

133
00:10:10,520 --> 00:10:11,320
Working with you

134
00:10:11,560 --> 00:10:12,880
has been quite pleasant so far.

135
00:10:13,360 --> 00:10:13,760
It ends

136
00:10:15,333 --> 00:10:16,466
if things go south.

137
00:10:28,560 --> 00:10:29,880
Who's bothering you this late?

138
00:10:29,888 --> 00:10:31,000
Your phone's blowing up.

139
00:10:31,160 --> 00:10:32,320
It's my dad.

140
00:10:33,200 --> 00:10:34,640
He sent a bunch of apartment listings

141
00:10:34,640 --> 00:10:35,840
all at once.

142
00:10:36,520 --> 00:10:37,640
Have you listed the place?

143
00:10:38,560 --> 00:10:39,360
Any inquiries?

144
00:10:39,444 --> 00:10:40,888
The housing market is terrible.

145
00:10:41,355 --> 00:10:42,720
I had to drop the price a bit.

146
00:10:42,960 --> 00:10:44,000
The agent said it was

147
00:10:44,000 --> 00:10:44,990
the only way to sell it.

148
00:10:45,080 --> 00:10:45,640
Plus,

149
00:10:46,000 --> 00:10:46,955
I'm in a rush to sell.

150
00:10:47,480 --> 00:10:48,920
The requirements I gave my dad were

151
00:10:49,360 --> 00:10:50,280
cheap rent,

152
00:10:50,360 --> 00:10:51,533
convenient transportation,

153
00:10:51,800 --> 00:10:52,640
and three bedrooms.

154
00:10:53,760 --> 00:10:54,520
Why so proactive?

155
00:10:55,760 --> 00:10:57,240
I was afraid you guys would ditch me.

156
00:10:57,480 --> 00:10:58,880
So I took the initiative.

157
00:11:00,920 --> 00:11:02,280
Once we start making some money,

158
00:11:02,444 --> 00:11:03,440
I'll buy a bigger place.

159
00:11:03,960 --> 00:11:04,320
Great.

160
00:11:04,680 --> 00:11:05,400
I'll ask my dad.

161
00:11:06,760 --> 00:11:08,720
Let me forward these to our group chat.

162
00:11:09,320 --> 00:11:10,480
If you see anything you like,

163
00:11:10,480 --> 00:11:12,240
my dad can arrange a viewing anytime.

164
00:11:14,520 --> 00:11:14,920
Ms. Lin.

165
00:11:15,680 --> 00:11:17,880
You finally found
a favor my dad can help with.

166
00:11:21,240 --> 00:11:22,280
You can't escape us now.

167
00:11:30,640 --> 00:11:30,960
What...

168
00:11:34,080 --> 00:11:34,520
What is it?

169
00:11:39,400 --> 00:11:40,640
My dad sent something about you.

170
00:11:41,240 --> 00:11:41,880
Me?

171
00:11:42,800 --> 00:11:43,960
Things about Zhou Mei?

172
00:11:44,400 --> 00:11:45,444
What is this about?

173
00:11:48,080 --> 00:11:49,200
My dad

174
00:11:49,880 --> 00:11:51,880
knows a lot of rich wives, right?

175
00:11:52,480 --> 00:11:53,520
You know how it is.

176
00:11:53,800 --> 00:11:56,600
Whenever a good property pops up,
he sends it to them.

177
00:11:56,840 --> 00:11:58,000
They can buy it on a whim.

178
00:11:58,480 --> 00:11:59,333
Get to the point.

179
00:12:01,480 --> 00:12:02,080
So...

180
00:12:02,840 --> 00:12:04,640
In that wives' group chat,

181
00:12:05,400 --> 00:12:07,200
someone posted a photo of Mei

182
00:12:08,080 --> 00:12:09,160
with her business profile.

183
00:12:10,200 --> 00:12:11,560
Why? What for?

184
00:12:12,000 --> 00:12:12,840
What do you think?

185
00:12:13,200 --> 00:12:14,640
"Beware of this homewrecker."

186
00:12:16,400 --> 00:12:18,200
I'll just read it out loud.

187
00:12:20,000 --> 00:12:21,240
(She has the face of a seductress.)
"Watch closely.

188
00:12:21,240 --> 00:12:22,680
(Don't let her exploit vulnerabilities.)
Are your husbands

189
00:12:22,680 --> 00:12:24,280
(I don't want any more victims.)
associating with this woman?

190
00:12:24,640 --> 00:12:25,400
If so, you must...

191
00:12:27,000 --> 00:12:27,440
You must

192
00:12:28,440 --> 00:12:30,040
beware of this gold digger.

193
00:12:31,240 --> 00:12:33,920
She has cost Mr. Bei six million yuan.

194
00:12:34,720 --> 00:12:36,840
If a hotshot like Mr. Bei
lost money to her,

195
00:12:36,840 --> 00:12:38,040
imagine what she's capable of."

196
00:12:39,000 --> 00:12:39,440
That's it.

197
00:12:47,560 --> 00:12:48,560
Who posted this?

198
00:12:50,080 --> 00:12:52,000
It must have started with Mrs. Bei.

199
00:12:52,560 --> 00:12:54,480
No one else knows about this matter

200
00:12:54,490 --> 00:12:55,440
except Mrs. Bei, Mr. Bei

201
00:12:55,520 --> 00:12:56,360
Zhang Yousen and me.

202
00:12:58,520 --> 00:13:00,200
Will this affect you, Mei?

203
00:13:01,800 --> 00:13:02,240
No.

204
00:13:03,240 --> 00:13:04,240
It's just a bit annoying.

205
00:13:04,920 --> 00:13:06,160
I'll have to deal with gossip.

206
00:13:12,240 --> 00:13:13,080
Is she okay?

207
00:13:13,777 --> 00:13:15,933
When it comes to
handling people like them,

208
00:13:16,360 --> 00:13:17,280
she never loses.

209
00:14:00,040 --> 00:14:01,520
They're carving up your client list.

210
00:14:01,555 --> 00:14:03,520
The gossipers went
to the Boss this morning.

211
00:14:03,760 --> 00:14:04,840
Led by the worst of them,

212
00:14:05,240 --> 00:14:07,400
they rattled off your list
of married male clients.

213
00:14:07,560 --> 00:14:09,160
They said you'd jeopardize the clients,

214
00:14:09,400 --> 00:14:10,520
that they want to help

215
00:14:10,866 --> 00:14:12,200
and retain these major clients.

216
00:14:13,480 --> 00:14:14,040
Got it.

217
00:14:14,760 --> 00:14:16,080
My clients used to be mine.

218
00:14:16,760 --> 00:14:17,280
From now on,

219
00:14:17,720 --> 00:14:18,960
I'll make sure their clients

220
00:14:19,040 --> 00:14:19,800
become mine, too.

221
00:14:21,000 --> 00:14:22,040
They know your clients

222
00:14:22,040 --> 00:14:23,440
better than you do.

223
00:14:23,560 --> 00:14:23,960
You know?

224
00:14:24,533 --> 00:14:26,022
What intel did you provide?

225
00:14:26,777 --> 00:14:28,200
I just provided emotional support.

226
00:14:28,320 --> 00:14:29,680
I trashed you left and right.

227
00:14:30,400 --> 00:14:31,600
I am the grandmaster

228
00:14:32,120 --> 00:14:33,800
of adding fuel to the fire.

229
00:14:34,777 --> 00:14:36,680
Didn't they give you any of my clients?

230
00:14:37,120 --> 00:14:38,120
Please.

231
00:14:38,240 --> 00:14:39,680
The mid-to-senior executives

232
00:14:39,680 --> 00:14:40,630
are all Iron Ladies now.

233
00:14:40,640 --> 00:14:42,000
I'm too busy serving them.

234
00:14:44,680 --> 00:14:45,400
Are you done?

235
00:14:45,600 --> 00:14:46,560
Hurry up and leave.

236
00:14:46,644 --> 00:14:47,560
Stop blocking the way

237
00:14:47,760 --> 00:14:48,640
like you always do.

238
00:14:49,244 --> 00:14:50,920
A peacock would've
taken up less space.

239
00:14:52,680 --> 00:14:53,480
Excuse me.

240
00:14:53,822 --> 00:14:55,155
What is that supposed to mean?

241
00:14:56,200 --> 00:14:57,240
You spit when you talk.

242
00:14:57,640 --> 00:14:58,120
It's gross.

243
00:15:01,266 --> 00:15:02,680
I really want to curse her out.

244
00:15:03,640 --> 00:15:04,560
Alright, calm down.

245
00:15:05,000 --> 00:15:06,080
Her days are numbered.

246
00:15:07,488 --> 00:15:08,720
How did it go with the Boss?

247
00:15:09,440 --> 00:15:10,760
Does the Boss know the rich wives

248
00:15:10,760 --> 00:15:11,560
publicly shamed her?

249
00:15:12,160 --> 00:15:12,800
She knows.

250
00:15:13,560 --> 00:15:14,600
She was already planning

251
00:15:14,600 --> 00:15:16,360
to discuss her role today.

252
00:15:18,160 --> 00:15:20,280
What goes around comes around.

253
00:15:21,480 --> 00:15:22,200
You mean Zhou Mei?

254
00:15:23,640 --> 00:15:24,360
Who else?

255
00:15:26,022 --> 00:15:26,800
Six million yuan.

256
00:15:27,760 --> 00:15:28,520
It takes

257
00:15:28,520 --> 00:15:30,320
skills to make a man
cough up six million.

258
00:15:30,888 --> 00:15:31,920
He didn't pay it for me.

259
00:15:32,640 --> 00:15:34,120
His own business had issues.

260
00:15:34,288 --> 00:15:36,444
I don't need a man
to spend six million on me.

261
00:15:38,200 --> 00:15:38,960
You've been

262
00:15:39,320 --> 00:15:40,080
popular lately.

263
00:15:41,600 --> 00:15:43,000
Since last night,

264
00:15:43,240 --> 00:15:44,480
ninety percent of the calls

265
00:15:44,520 --> 00:15:46,160
on my phone have been about you.

266
00:15:47,960 --> 00:15:49,000
If these rumors

267
00:15:49,000 --> 00:15:50,680
are causing issues
for my clients at home,

268
00:15:50,880 --> 00:15:52,520
you can reassign their accounts

269
00:15:52,720 --> 00:15:53,520
if they agree to it.

270
00:15:54,280 --> 00:15:54,800
But Boss,

271
00:15:55,360 --> 00:15:56,080
I doubt I'll lose

272
00:15:56,080 --> 00:15:56,920
any of my clients.

273
00:15:57,111 --> 00:15:58,840
I wouldn't have
lasted this long otherwise.

274
00:16:00,200 --> 00:16:01,360
In sales,

275
00:16:01,360 --> 00:16:02,150
it's not just women.

276
00:16:02,160 --> 00:16:03,000
It's mostly men.

277
00:16:03,088 --> 00:16:05,311
Anyone trying
to poach my clients is mistaken.

278
00:16:05,880 --> 00:16:07,440
I make more money not by competing

279
00:16:07,800 --> 00:16:08,720
against women,

280
00:16:09,044 --> 00:16:09,760
but against men.

281
00:16:13,280 --> 00:16:14,360
I haven't said anything.

282
00:16:16,160 --> 00:16:17,200
Yet, you lectured me.

283
00:16:17,920 --> 00:16:18,320
What?

284
00:16:19,880 --> 00:16:21,000
You act like you don't care,

285
00:16:22,000 --> 00:16:23,120
but you clearly do.

286
00:16:25,560 --> 00:16:26,480
I do care.

287
00:16:27,577 --> 00:16:29,560
I've known some clients
for seven or eight years.

288
00:16:30,200 --> 00:16:31,000
I've nurtured

289
00:16:31,000 --> 00:16:31,960
these relationships.

290
00:16:31,960 --> 00:16:33,244
Did I tell you what the calls

291
00:16:33,520 --> 00:16:34,280
were about?

292
00:16:36,120 --> 00:16:36,760
What about?

293
00:16:37,240 --> 00:16:39,240
A large part was just gossip, of course.

294
00:16:39,880 --> 00:16:40,840
But others

295
00:16:41,533 --> 00:16:42,840
were calling to work with you.

296
00:16:45,480 --> 00:16:46,360
Partner with me?

297
00:16:47,200 --> 00:16:48,400
It's a PR firm.

298
00:16:49,360 --> 00:16:51,040
What they need
is connections, resources,

299
00:16:51,240 --> 00:16:53,600
EQ, and crisis management skills.

300
00:16:54,480 --> 00:16:56,080
In your scandal with Mr. Bei,

301
00:16:56,466 --> 00:16:58,840
you demonstrated all three perfectly.

302
00:17:03,120 --> 00:17:03,720
So, Boss,

303
00:17:04,200 --> 00:17:05,280
are you saying

304
00:17:05,600 --> 00:17:06,680
you want new clients

305
00:17:06,720 --> 00:17:07,760
to replace my old ones?

306
00:17:07,880 --> 00:17:09,440
Who was just telling me

307
00:17:09,440 --> 00:17:10,720
that she is irreplaceable

308
00:17:11,480 --> 00:17:12,520
to her old clients?

309
00:17:14,200 --> 00:17:15,760
So turn off your internal alarm.

310
00:17:17,800 --> 00:17:19,560
If I'm so important to the company,

311
00:17:20,360 --> 00:17:21,240
does that mean

312
00:17:21,400 --> 00:17:22,320
I can make a request?

313
00:17:26,755 --> 00:17:28,400
What about the game rights for "Tao Yao:

314
00:17:28,400 --> 00:17:29,050
Dream of Wuchuan"?

315
00:17:29,080 --> 00:17:29,680
The same offer.

316
00:17:31,040 --> 00:17:32,480
It's a reasonable deal for us.

317
00:17:33,520 --> 00:17:34,680
Their boss is a fan of He Han.

318
00:17:34,755 --> 00:17:37,377
Even after what happened,
they're willing to stick to the price.

319
00:17:38,120 --> 00:17:39,240
This money is our lifeline.

320
00:17:39,800 --> 00:17:41,400
He Han rejected the offer because it was

321
00:17:41,520 --> 00:17:41,920
too low.

322
00:17:42,822 --> 00:17:43,920
Get the contract moving.

323
00:17:44,111 --> 00:17:45,680
Legally, the copyright belongs to us.

324
00:17:45,733 --> 00:17:46,600
But morally speaking,

325
00:17:46,720 --> 00:17:47,920
I should inform He Han.

326
00:17:48,280 --> 00:17:48,640
Okay.

327
00:17:49,360 --> 00:17:50,320
What's with Gu Yan?

328
00:17:50,822 --> 00:17:52,160
I tested the waters with him.

329
00:17:52,160 --> 00:17:54,244
He doesn't seem interested
in starting a new novel.

330
00:17:54,400 --> 00:17:55,600
He said that's what you wanted.

331
00:17:55,777 --> 00:17:56,920
He wanted to write a sequel

332
00:17:56,920 --> 00:17:58,210
to "Parting with Yan Dan at Yishui".

333
00:17:58,222 --> 00:17:59,333
You didn't approve it.

334
00:18:00,000 --> 00:18:01,200
He swore up and down

335
00:18:01,280 --> 00:18:02,000
that he had

336
00:18:02,000 --> 00:18:03,377
the energy to start a project.

337
00:18:04,133 --> 00:18:04,920
What about Sansan?

338
00:18:05,422 --> 00:18:07,040
Aside from Mr. Fan and Zhao Lanxin,

339
00:18:07,040 --> 00:18:08,480
nobody else knows Sansan's identity.

340
00:18:08,680 --> 00:18:10,160
The credited editor is Zhao Lanxin.

341
00:18:10,160 --> 00:18:12,311
The contact for
Dingqi Reading Platform is Mr. Fan.

342
00:18:12,600 --> 00:18:13,720
No one else has handled it.

343
00:18:14,560 --> 00:18:15,320
Is it possible

344
00:18:15,320 --> 00:18:17,080
she's doing what you did with Gu Yan?

345
00:18:17,600 --> 00:18:18,760
Hiding her own secret weapon?

346
00:18:19,280 --> 00:18:20,000
Unlikely.

347
00:18:21,240 --> 00:18:22,160
It's either

348
00:18:22,240 --> 00:18:23,280
a sensitive background

349
00:18:23,760 --> 00:18:24,840
or they're a famous author

350
00:18:24,911 --> 00:18:25,840
using a new pen name.

351
00:18:26,400 --> 00:18:26,960
Hong Qigong?

352
00:18:27,755 --> 00:18:29,000
Different writing styles.

353
00:18:30,160 --> 00:18:31,080
Is it possible

354
00:18:31,080 --> 00:18:32,160
she changed her style?

355
00:18:35,600 --> 00:18:36,720
Changing one's writing style

356
00:18:38,080 --> 00:18:38,800
is very difficult.

357
00:18:44,960 --> 00:18:46,320
Three bowls of wontons.

358
00:18:47,200 --> 00:18:48,000
Your steamed buns.

359
00:18:48,010 --> 00:18:48,880
- Thanks.
- That's everything.

360
00:18:48,880 --> 00:18:49,520
I already paid.

361
00:18:49,520 --> 00:18:51,222
- Great.
- Condiments are over there.

362
00:19:21,840 --> 00:19:22,360
Who is it?

363
00:19:48,720 --> 00:19:50,600
You're here about the new project?

364
00:19:53,600 --> 00:19:54,080
Yeah.

365
00:19:54,760 --> 00:19:55,920
You said you had the time

366
00:19:56,120 --> 00:19:57,280
to start another one.

367
00:20:00,440 --> 00:20:01,600
At the time,

368
00:20:01,960 --> 00:20:03,720
I really wanted to write a sequel.

369
00:20:04,360 --> 00:20:05,480
That's why I said that.

370
00:20:06,560 --> 00:20:07,600
Later, I realized

371
00:20:08,840 --> 00:20:09,800
I overpromised.

372
00:20:11,577 --> 00:20:13,640
But you've been submitting
your drafts on time.

373
00:20:15,160 --> 00:20:16,040
You told me

374
00:20:17,680 --> 00:20:19,360
if I want to do this long-term,

375
00:20:19,960 --> 00:20:20,680
I need a routine.

376
00:20:22,400 --> 00:20:24,320
I've been telling you that since we met.

377
00:20:25,244 --> 00:20:26,600
But you never took it seriously.

378
00:20:29,120 --> 00:20:29,840
Why so disciplined

379
00:20:30,400 --> 00:20:31,560
all of a sudden?

380
00:20:39,555 --> 00:20:40,600
Submitting drafts on time

381
00:20:41,040 --> 00:20:42,000
gives me time

382
00:20:42,920 --> 00:20:44,360
to play games and relax.

383
00:20:45,960 --> 00:20:47,040
A good work-life balance

384
00:20:47,866 --> 00:20:48,760
makes the pressure

385
00:20:49,280 --> 00:20:50,080
feel manageable.

386
00:20:53,422 --> 00:20:55,244
You haven't reached out much lately.

387
00:20:55,920 --> 00:20:57,280
Isn't that what you wanted?

388
00:20:58,520 --> 00:20:59,680
Submitting drafts on time,

389
00:21:00,200 --> 00:21:01,040
maintaining quality,

390
00:21:02,080 --> 00:21:04,288
and not taking up
too much of your time and space.

391
00:21:05,560 --> 00:21:07,120
That's the expected behavior

392
00:21:07,240 --> 00:21:08,960
of a mature, independent author.

393
00:21:09,920 --> 00:21:11,440
I did want you to grow up.

394
00:21:11,960 --> 00:21:12,760
I have.

395
00:21:15,040 --> 00:21:16,120
That way, you have the time

396
00:21:16,120 --> 00:21:17,120
to develop other authors

397
00:21:17,600 --> 00:21:18,840
and help them grow, right?

398
00:21:19,800 --> 00:21:21,600
In theory, as an editor

399
00:21:21,840 --> 00:21:22,520
or a boss,

400
00:21:23,080 --> 00:21:24,880
that's what I should be planning.

401
00:21:26,800 --> 00:21:28,360
But our situation now is different.

402
00:21:29,760 --> 00:21:30,560
So I'm hoping

403
00:21:31,160 --> 00:21:32,400
you can stand by my side

404
00:21:33,022 --> 00:21:33,760
and help Chenxing

405
00:21:33,888 --> 00:21:35,600
get through this difficult time.

406
00:21:38,200 --> 00:21:40,440
I'm glad to hear you say you need me.

407
00:21:41,480 --> 00:21:42,600
Because I always thought

408
00:21:42,866 --> 00:21:44,000
that I was the only one

409
00:21:44,000 --> 00:21:45,040
who needed you.

410
00:21:45,280 --> 00:21:46,560
Yes, I need you.

411
00:21:47,200 --> 00:21:49,000
I need you to start a new project.

412
00:21:49,600 --> 00:21:51,800
So the company can
rely on you for more income

413
00:21:52,120 --> 00:21:53,360
to keep operations running.

414
00:21:54,000 --> 00:21:55,000
Why didn't you let me

415
00:21:55,000 --> 00:21:56,400
write the sequel back then?

416
00:21:56,466 --> 00:21:57,920
We wouldn't have these problems now.

417
00:21:58,240 --> 00:21:59,880
That was Mr. Fan's advertising project.

418
00:22:00,622 --> 00:22:02,040
A sequel to Phantom Knight

419
00:22:02,040 --> 00:22:04,080
wouldn't have added
much to your personal value.

420
00:22:14,600 --> 00:22:15,760
You're going to like

421
00:22:16,080 --> 00:22:16,840
the story I have.

422
00:22:21,800 --> 00:22:22,600
I told you.

423
00:22:24,360 --> 00:22:26,320
I don't have the energy
to juggle two projects.

424
00:22:33,280 --> 00:22:34,920
Chenxing and I

425
00:22:35,680 --> 00:22:36,400
need your help.

426
00:22:45,200 --> 00:22:46,400
Finish what you're working on.

427
00:22:46,600 --> 00:22:47,760
Look at it when you have time

428
00:22:48,000 --> 00:22:48,880
before you decide.

429
00:22:50,800 --> 00:22:51,955
I'll wait to hear from you.

430
00:23:43,900 --> 00:23:44,940
(The old man pointed
at the chessboard and said,)

431
00:23:44,940 --> 00:23:46,060
("Every move represents destiny.)

432
00:23:46,060 --> 00:23:48,900
(Your fates are like the pieces,
manipulated by others...")

433
00:23:53,080 --> 00:23:54,200
I'm so sick of this.

434
00:23:55,280 --> 00:23:57,120
HR is absolutely useless.

435
00:23:57,480 --> 00:23:58,920
Shouldn't Zhou Mei get transferred?

436
00:23:59,200 --> 00:24:00,240
Why is it you?

437
00:24:01,160 --> 00:24:02,320
What did the Boss tell you?

438
00:24:02,960 --> 00:24:03,880
The Boss just said

439
00:24:04,240 --> 00:24:05,640
they're preparing to restructure

440
00:24:05,640 --> 00:24:06,640
our current accounts.

441
00:24:07,480 --> 00:24:09,280
Shouldn't Zhou Mei be kicked out?

442
00:24:10,560 --> 00:24:11,680
Did you tell the Boss

443
00:24:11,680 --> 00:24:12,680
your husband and in-laws

444
00:24:12,800 --> 00:24:14,040
are all in Beijing,

445
00:24:14,066 --> 00:24:15,240
so they're sending you there?

446
00:24:15,280 --> 00:24:16,320
I didn't.

447
00:24:17,280 --> 00:24:19,040
I said the rest of us
have some bandwidth,

448
00:24:19,177 --> 00:24:21,080
and we want
to contribute more to the company.

449
00:24:22,160 --> 00:24:24,040
You should have
just said you have bandwidth!

450
00:24:24,040 --> 00:24:25,280
Why drag us into it?

451
00:24:26,440 --> 00:24:27,440
I'm so sick of this.

452
00:24:28,600 --> 00:24:29,360
What about

453
00:24:29,360 --> 00:24:30,880
your local clients in Shanghai?

454
00:24:31,933 --> 00:24:33,560
Well, we definitely have the bandwidth

455
00:24:33,560 --> 00:24:34,320
to take those over.

456
00:24:35,400 --> 00:24:36,200
Excuse me.

457
00:24:36,760 --> 00:24:37,840
Sorry to interrupt.

458
00:24:44,360 --> 00:24:45,840
The Boss told me to take over

459
00:24:45,840 --> 00:24:47,080
your Shanghai clients.

460
00:24:47,640 --> 00:24:48,720
Whenever you have time,

461
00:24:48,760 --> 00:24:49,866
let me buy you a coffee.

462
00:24:53,440 --> 00:24:54,640
Those three women out there,

463
00:24:55,120 --> 00:24:56,760
can we fire at least one of them?

464
00:24:58,480 --> 00:25:00,200
Their combined sales numbers

465
00:25:00,280 --> 00:25:01,400
exactly equal mine alone.

466
00:25:02,040 --> 00:25:02,760
If one leaves,

467
00:25:02,911 --> 00:25:03,800
I'll take her clients,

468
00:25:04,200 --> 00:25:05,320
and you save on a salary.

469
00:25:06,680 --> 00:25:09,040
Show some mercy when you can.

470
00:25:10,444 --> 00:25:11,680
That's what I wanted to say.

471
00:25:15,955 --> 00:25:17,880
You really know
how to make women hate you.

472
00:25:19,080 --> 00:25:19,720
I'm a woman.

473
00:25:19,840 --> 00:25:21,520
I know exactly why they hate you.

474
00:25:22,400 --> 00:25:23,080
I value you

475
00:25:23,920 --> 00:25:25,280
because I am a boss.

476
00:25:26,880 --> 00:25:28,200
I know what kind of employee

477
00:25:28,200 --> 00:25:29,320
is more important.

478
00:25:30,640 --> 00:25:31,080
So,

479
00:25:32,040 --> 00:25:33,360
keep proving your worth.

480
00:25:34,200 --> 00:25:34,760
Yes, Boss.

481
00:25:36,040 --> 00:25:37,040
I won't let you down.

482
00:25:37,480 --> 00:25:39,040
Why do we have to hand them over to you?

483
00:25:40,360 --> 00:25:42,120
The three of us are the closest.

484
00:25:42,400 --> 00:25:44,120
Our clients are interconnected.

485
00:25:44,244 --> 00:25:45,480
We see each other all the time.

486
00:25:45,640 --> 00:25:46,520
I'm going to the Boss.

487
00:25:47,360 --> 00:25:48,280
That wouldn't be wise.

488
00:25:49,000 --> 00:25:50,200
Stop bragging about how close

489
00:25:50,200 --> 00:25:51,200
the three of you are.

490
00:25:51,880 --> 00:25:53,040
Otherwise, the Boss might just

491
00:25:53,080 --> 00:25:54,200
send you all to Beijing.

492
00:25:54,333 --> 00:25:55,480
They are short-staffed there.

493
00:25:56,640 --> 00:25:57,600
I'm not scared.

494
00:25:58,400 --> 00:25:59,640
The one being transferred

495
00:25:59,840 --> 00:26:01,440
should have been you in the first place.

496
00:26:01,680 --> 00:26:03,120
Because you said I was a liability.

497
00:26:04,080 --> 00:26:06,000
The Boss is keeping me in Shanghai.

498
00:26:06,200 --> 00:26:07,560
Doesn't that solve your problem?

499
00:26:08,600 --> 00:26:09,360
What problem?

500
00:26:11,160 --> 00:26:11,760
What happened?

501
00:26:12,120 --> 00:26:14,040
Nothing, yet you claimed
I was a problem.

502
00:26:14,355 --> 00:26:15,480
Watch it, or I'll sue you.

503
00:26:18,066 --> 00:26:19,200
Are you close with them?

504
00:26:19,640 --> 00:26:20,560
Care to go to Beijing?

505
00:26:23,320 --> 00:26:24,800
Now I'm really mad.

506
00:26:26,711 --> 00:26:28,200
You messed with the wrong person.

507
00:26:34,740 --> 00:26:36,180
(Shrimp and Fresh Meat)

508
00:26:46,320 --> 00:26:47,640
That scared me to death.

509
00:26:48,040 --> 00:26:48,600
I felt like

510
00:26:48,600 --> 00:26:49,990
I was acting in "Infernal Affairs".

511
00:26:50,120 --> 00:26:51,200
It's so exhausting.

512
00:26:51,880 --> 00:26:52,400
My gosh.

513
00:26:53,160 --> 00:26:54,280
I need some orange juice

514
00:26:54,480 --> 00:26:55,466
to regain my strength.

515
00:27:01,360 --> 00:27:02,280
How was my acting?

516
00:27:02,600 --> 00:27:03,160
Manly, right?

517
00:27:03,560 --> 00:27:04,800
Good enough for an Oscar?

518
00:27:05,160 --> 00:27:05,800
Brilliant.

519
00:27:07,440 --> 00:27:08,600
But I think White Tea

520
00:27:08,600 --> 00:27:10,288
probably wants
to take you to Beijing.

521
00:27:10,720 --> 00:27:12,400
Between Black Tea, Green Tea, and you,

522
00:27:12,520 --> 00:27:13,760
she has to pick someone.

523
00:27:15,320 --> 00:27:16,320
If she's thinking that,

524
00:27:16,320 --> 00:27:17,680
you have to save me!

525
00:27:18,680 --> 00:27:19,160
Your hand.

526
00:27:20,160 --> 00:27:20,560
What for?

527
00:27:23,360 --> 00:27:24,120
Your protection.

528
00:27:25,377 --> 00:27:26,720
If White Tea drags you away,

529
00:27:27,240 --> 00:27:28,040
tell the Boss

530
00:27:28,200 --> 00:27:29,600
that Black Tea has a major client

531
00:27:29,720 --> 00:27:31,360
moving to Beijing
for their kid's school.

532
00:27:31,880 --> 00:27:33,000
She didn't tell the Boss,

533
00:27:33,000 --> 00:27:34,600
so the Beijing team can't take them.

534
00:27:35,155 --> 00:27:36,888
Then, I won't wait
for her to drag me down.

535
00:27:36,911 --> 00:27:39,044
I'm going straight
to the Boss after this.

536
00:27:39,640 --> 00:27:40,960
They never could have guessed

537
00:27:40,960 --> 00:27:42,088
that trying to rat you out

538
00:27:42,320 --> 00:27:43,320
would backfire

539
00:27:43,720 --> 00:27:44,400
so spectacularly.

540
00:27:45,640 --> 00:27:46,560
How did you find out?

541
00:27:47,760 --> 00:27:48,760
They always pick on me.

542
00:27:48,760 --> 00:27:50,160
I have to be prepared.

543
00:27:51,160 --> 00:27:51,840
Brilliant.

544
00:27:56,900 --> 00:28:01,020
(Mrs. Bei)

545
00:28:09,120 --> 00:28:12,440
Hasn't He Han always
been at the top of the list?

546
00:28:12,880 --> 00:28:14,320
The only reason he isn't this time

547
00:28:14,320 --> 00:28:15,777
is because of the recent backlash.

548
00:28:16,120 --> 00:28:17,240
Didn't I tell you?

549
00:28:17,240 --> 00:28:19,240
I'll handle the backlash.

550
00:28:19,800 --> 00:28:20,920
Without the resources,

551
00:28:21,200 --> 00:28:22,240
how can I make money?

552
00:28:22,555 --> 00:28:24,422
The fans of our top two books
have flocked

553
00:28:24,440 --> 00:28:26,422
to the "Parting with Yan Dan
at Yishui" fan group.

554
00:28:26,840 --> 00:28:28,040
Was that your doing?

555
00:28:29,760 --> 00:28:31,120
Those are VIPs.

556
00:28:31,120 --> 00:28:32,840
You think I could sway them?

557
00:28:35,240 --> 00:28:36,720
They like He Han,

558
00:28:37,200 --> 00:28:38,360
but that doesn't stop them

559
00:28:38,360 --> 00:28:39,760
from liking other authors.

560
00:28:40,480 --> 00:28:41,960
They can tip He Han,

561
00:28:42,360 --> 00:28:42,800
and still

562
00:28:43,160 --> 00:28:44,440
go over to

563
00:28:44,450 --> 00:28:45,710
"Parting with Yan Dan at Yishui"

564
00:28:45,720 --> 00:28:46,680
and tip there, too.

565
00:28:46,880 --> 00:28:48,000
It's their choice.

566
00:28:48,720 --> 00:28:49,280
Nobody should

567
00:28:49,480 --> 00:28:51,120
put all their eggs in one basket.

568
00:28:51,777 --> 00:28:52,800
Who are you talking about?

569
00:28:53,000 --> 00:28:53,520
Who?

570
00:28:54,000 --> 00:28:55,320
I mean nobody.

571
00:28:56,040 --> 00:28:57,080
Me, you,

572
00:28:58,040 --> 00:28:59,160
and even He Han.

573
00:28:59,880 --> 00:29:00,440
Us.

574
00:29:02,040 --> 00:29:02,520
He Han.

575
00:29:03,520 --> 00:29:04,640
Can you please sit down?

576
00:29:05,777 --> 00:29:06,560
What is he doing?

577
00:29:06,760 --> 00:29:07,560
Riding a bike?

578
00:29:08,520 --> 00:29:10,680
Did you say
the same thing to Zhao Lanxin?

579
00:29:11,440 --> 00:29:12,240
"Us"?

580
00:29:12,760 --> 00:29:13,720
That "us"

581
00:29:14,440 --> 00:29:16,440
is different from this "us."

582
00:29:17,080 --> 00:29:18,480
With her, it's strictly business.

583
00:29:19,240 --> 00:29:20,680
Between us,

584
00:29:21,288 --> 00:29:22,120
it's about loyalty.

585
00:29:24,120 --> 00:29:24,680
Fan.

586
00:29:25,600 --> 00:29:27,960
Only what translates
into cold, hard cash

587
00:29:28,400 --> 00:29:30,040
is true loyalty.

588
00:29:30,320 --> 00:29:31,440
Just be patient, okay?

589
00:29:32,920 --> 00:29:34,760
Remember the former editor

590
00:29:35,440 --> 00:29:37,000
for Phantom Knight, Ma?

591
00:29:37,400 --> 00:29:38,880
I've been talking to him lately.

592
00:29:40,040 --> 00:29:41,000
This guy, Ma...

593
00:29:43,680 --> 00:29:44,280
He Han.

594
00:29:45,200 --> 00:29:45,800
He Han.

595
00:29:46,400 --> 00:29:47,840
The Phantom Knight team

596
00:29:47,840 --> 00:29:49,480
might release a statement soon.

597
00:29:50,440 --> 00:29:53,200
They're willing to endorse
your "Shattered Six States".

598
00:29:56,200 --> 00:29:57,720
Fan, are you for real?

599
00:29:57,920 --> 00:29:59,520
I certainly hope it's real.

600
00:29:59,760 --> 00:30:00,880
That's why I've been working

601
00:30:01,640 --> 00:30:02,440
tirelessly on it.

602
00:30:04,200 --> 00:30:05,120
How do you prove

603
00:30:05,320 --> 00:30:07,440
the statement is actually
from Phantom Knight?

604
00:30:08,040 --> 00:30:09,840
That's exactly the tricky part.

605
00:30:09,880 --> 00:30:11,400
It depends on whether Phantom Knight

606
00:30:11,400 --> 00:30:13,480
is willing to reveal his identity.

607
00:30:14,440 --> 00:30:15,160
If he does,

608
00:30:15,333 --> 00:30:17,377
it'll be a massive event
in the literary world.

609
00:30:17,720 --> 00:30:18,120
Of course.

610
00:30:18,880 --> 00:30:19,920
If this gets handled

611
00:30:20,640 --> 00:30:21,680
this way,

612
00:30:23,040 --> 00:30:25,200
doesn't that resolve He Han's crisis?

613
00:30:25,680 --> 00:30:26,120
Right?

614
00:30:26,960 --> 00:30:27,440
So,

615
00:30:28,040 --> 00:30:28,560
just wait.

616
00:30:29,640 --> 00:30:30,480
I'm afraid we can't.

617
00:30:35,000 --> 00:30:35,640
Why not?

618
00:30:36,622 --> 00:30:38,600
I plan to
end "Shattered Six States" early.

619
00:30:44,520 --> 00:30:45,160
Why?

620
00:30:45,720 --> 00:30:46,360
It's annoying.

621
00:30:46,600 --> 00:30:48,600
Ending it early saves a lot of trouble.

622
00:30:49,640 --> 00:30:50,800
When you say early,

623
00:30:51,400 --> 00:30:52,800
how early do you mean?

624
00:30:53,600 --> 00:30:54,360
Within three days.

625
00:30:58,320 --> 00:30:58,720
You're...

626
00:30:59,040 --> 00:31:00,600
You're just speaking out of spite.

627
00:31:02,444 --> 00:31:04,520
Aren't you going to publish
what you've written?

628
00:31:06,040 --> 00:31:06,600
No.

629
00:31:10,280 --> 00:31:11,160
I'll talk to He Han.

630
00:31:11,160 --> 00:31:11,760
You head back.

631
00:31:12,680 --> 00:31:13,600
No, He Han.

632
00:31:14,320 --> 00:31:16,120
It's impossible to end it in three days.

633
00:31:16,840 --> 00:31:18,720
Didn't you just introduce a new map?

634
00:31:18,840 --> 00:31:20,360
Who do you think makes up the new map?

635
00:31:20,600 --> 00:31:21,880
Three days or three months,

636
00:31:21,880 --> 00:31:23,444
doesn't it depend on how I write it?

637
00:31:23,680 --> 00:31:24,880
Even being generous,

638
00:31:25,280 --> 00:31:26,480
we've only written

639
00:31:26,480 --> 00:31:27,920
not even half

640
00:31:27,955 --> 00:31:29,040
of what's in the outline.

641
00:31:29,040 --> 00:31:30,400
That's a terrible ending!

642
00:31:31,600 --> 00:31:32,280
Listen to me.

643
00:31:32,920 --> 00:31:34,760
We have a contract!

644
00:31:35,480 --> 00:31:36,600
You'll be held liable.

645
00:31:36,600 --> 00:31:37,866
It has a beginning and an end.

646
00:31:37,870 --> 00:31:38,720
It's a proper ending.

647
00:31:38,720 --> 00:31:39,760
How is it not terrible?

648
00:31:39,960 --> 00:31:40,480
The story...

649
00:31:40,480 --> 00:31:41,760
Go back. Let me talk to him.

650
00:31:41,760 --> 00:31:42,200
The story...

651
00:31:42,200 --> 00:31:43,440
Forget the ending and the contract!

652
00:31:43,440 --> 00:31:45,444
- Don't we have an outline?
- Just stop talking, okay?

653
00:31:45,466 --> 00:31:45,880
Just go.

654
00:31:46,120 --> 00:31:46,800
Stop talking.

655
00:31:47,240 --> 00:31:48,480
How will you face your readers?

656
00:31:53,200 --> 00:31:54,320
I don't care, He Han.

657
00:31:54,760 --> 00:31:55,360
Alright.

658
00:31:56,155 --> 00:31:56,800
You go first.

659
00:31:56,800 --> 00:31:57,820
Talk some sense into him!

660
00:31:57,840 --> 00:31:58,200
I will.

661
00:32:06,040 --> 00:32:06,720
He's gone.

662
00:32:08,000 --> 00:32:09,000
Now tell me the truth.

663
00:32:09,280 --> 00:32:10,400
What are you really planning?

664
00:32:11,520 --> 00:32:12,120
I told you.

665
00:32:12,222 --> 00:32:14,422
I'm ending
"Shattered Six States" in three days.

666
00:32:14,440 --> 00:32:16,200
Your readers will tear you apart.

667
00:32:16,200 --> 00:32:17,160
They already are.

668
00:32:17,560 --> 00:32:18,760
Those are just

669
00:32:18,760 --> 00:32:20,680
Phantom Knight's old fans

670
00:32:20,840 --> 00:32:21,920
and some random

671
00:32:21,920 --> 00:32:22,880
bystanders.

672
00:32:22,920 --> 00:32:24,160
What about your own fans?

673
00:32:24,360 --> 00:32:25,520
They're still on your side.

674
00:32:26,240 --> 00:32:27,840
And as Fan mentioned,

675
00:32:27,960 --> 00:32:29,120
if Phantom Knight

676
00:32:29,120 --> 00:32:30,040
releases a statement,

677
00:32:30,040 --> 00:32:31,560
this will all blow over.

678
00:32:31,560 --> 00:32:33,760
My novel is my novel.

679
00:32:34,000 --> 00:32:35,320
My story, my voice.

680
00:32:35,600 --> 00:32:37,120
Why should someone else have to vouch

681
00:32:37,120 --> 00:32:39,040
for my own work?

682
00:32:39,200 --> 00:32:40,380
What if there's no statement?

683
00:32:40,560 --> 00:32:41,440
Am I the problem?

684
00:32:41,560 --> 00:32:42,600
Or my novel is?

685
00:32:42,720 --> 00:32:43,840
That's nonsense.

686
00:32:43,933 --> 00:32:45,160
I don't care about a statement.

687
00:32:45,170 --> 00:32:46,620
Once I finish "Shattered Six States",

688
00:32:46,640 --> 00:32:47,720
it's over.

689
00:32:47,760 --> 00:32:49,360
I'll just write a new story

690
00:32:49,600 --> 00:32:51,320
that's better than this one.

691
00:32:51,320 --> 00:32:52,160
You'll pay damages!

692
00:32:52,160 --> 00:32:52,760
Then I'll pay!

693
00:32:55,120 --> 00:32:57,360
I work for you to make money.

694
00:32:57,480 --> 00:32:58,711
How much more do you want?

695
00:32:59,320 --> 00:33:00,840
I'll give you every cent I have left.

696
00:33:00,840 --> 00:33:01,920
Will that do?

697
00:33:02,160 --> 00:33:02,600
Fine.

698
00:33:03,760 --> 00:33:04,320
I'll do it.

699
00:33:11,920 --> 00:33:12,800
Now I know

700
00:33:12,800 --> 00:33:14,880
why Lin Zhanqiao couldn't stand you.

701
00:33:15,200 --> 00:33:16,040
When things are easy,

702
00:33:16,244 --> 00:33:17,400
you're nice and smiling.

703
00:33:17,511 --> 00:33:18,360
But when they aren't,

704
00:33:18,480 --> 00:33:19,720
you flip the table and quit.

705
00:33:19,960 --> 00:33:21,280
You're an adult.

706
00:33:21,440 --> 00:33:22,720
You can't expect life

707
00:33:22,720 --> 00:33:24,400
to be smooth sailing every day!

708
00:33:24,600 --> 00:33:26,440
And you can't expect those around you

709
00:33:26,600 --> 00:33:28,200
to always have your back,

710
00:33:28,320 --> 00:33:29,500
tolerating every erratic mood

711
00:33:29,560 --> 00:33:30,640
and every outburst,

712
00:33:30,800 --> 00:33:31,680
while they pamper you

713
00:33:31,960 --> 00:33:33,240
and worship your attitude!

714
00:33:33,960 --> 00:33:34,640
Go figure it out!

715
00:34:19,920 --> 00:34:20,320
Hello?

716
00:34:22,080 --> 00:34:23,280
When are you free tonight?

717
00:34:25,360 --> 00:34:26,600
I have meetings all afternoon.

718
00:34:26,600 --> 00:34:28,480
Not sure when I'll be off.

719
00:34:29,355 --> 00:34:30,688
Let me know when you're done.

720
00:34:31,000 --> 00:34:31,360
Okay.

721
00:34:46,244 --> 00:34:47,720
The company's operational issues

722
00:34:47,720 --> 00:34:49,520
are a heavy burden for us.

723
00:34:50,520 --> 00:34:51,880
But I'll handle that.

724
00:34:52,155 --> 00:34:53,200
That pressure must not

725
00:34:53,440 --> 00:34:54,440
bleed into the project.

726
00:34:55,040 --> 00:34:56,000
Haste makes waste.

727
00:34:56,800 --> 00:34:58,440
We need to maintain

728
00:34:58,480 --> 00:34:59,840
our current development pace.

729
00:35:00,640 --> 00:35:01,400
A unique edge

730
00:35:03,240 --> 00:35:03,920
goes a long way.

731
00:35:05,040 --> 00:35:07,160
Quality over speed.

732
00:35:10,560 --> 00:35:11,000
Zhangzhu.

733
00:35:12,511 --> 00:35:14,040
Why are you distracted at work?

734
00:35:15,800 --> 00:35:17,520
Mr. He Han posted in the group

735
00:35:19,777 --> 00:35:21,880
that "Shattered Six States"
ends in three chapters.

736
00:35:23,360 --> 00:35:23,880
What? Why?

737
00:35:24,720 --> 00:35:26,280
He said he wants to write a new novel.

738
00:36:19,360 --> 00:36:20,000
Meeting's over?

739
00:36:24,000 --> 00:36:24,720
Are you here

740
00:36:26,160 --> 00:36:27,560
to tell me you're ending

741
00:36:28,160 --> 00:36:30,120
in three chapters and 10,000 words?

742
00:36:31,866 --> 00:36:33,320
It's the only way to stop you and Ma

743
00:36:33,320 --> 00:36:35,200
from trying to unmask Phantom Knight.

744
00:36:35,520 --> 00:36:36,600
Ma and Fan have only

745
00:36:36,600 --> 00:36:37,760
talked a few times.

746
00:36:38,000 --> 00:36:39,400
Fan is a shark.

747
00:36:40,360 --> 00:36:41,920
You think he'd pass up a gimmick

748
00:36:41,920 --> 00:36:43,680
like exposing Phantom Knight?

749
00:36:44,280 --> 00:36:44,920
He'd love for me

750
00:36:45,240 --> 00:36:46,920
to keep writing and taking the heat

751
00:36:47,200 --> 00:36:48,920
just to set up the big reveal.

752
00:36:49,640 --> 00:36:51,320
Everyone wants a piece of that drama.

753
00:36:54,960 --> 00:36:56,480
I have to end this now

754
00:36:57,080 --> 00:36:58,480
to catch him off guard.

755
00:36:58,560 --> 00:36:59,880
You're sabotaging your future.

756
00:37:00,920 --> 00:37:01,600
You have ways

757
00:37:01,600 --> 00:37:02,622
to solve this problem.

758
00:37:02,711 --> 00:37:04,400
Why choose a path where everyone loses?

759
00:37:04,400 --> 00:37:06,080
I'm not here to argue.

760
00:37:06,400 --> 00:37:07,377
I've made my decision.

761
00:37:07,640 --> 00:37:08,800
I'm just letting you know.

762
00:37:11,000 --> 00:37:12,240
You didn't have to notify me.

763
00:37:15,160 --> 00:37:16,000
Also...

764
00:37:18,320 --> 00:37:19,400
From now on,

765
00:37:20,488 --> 00:37:21,600
stay out of my business.

766
00:37:33,200 --> 00:37:34,600
I was your editor

767
00:37:35,733 --> 00:37:37,355
when "Shattered Six States" began.

768
00:37:40,640 --> 00:37:42,200
I want it to have a proper ending.

769
00:37:46,920 --> 00:37:47,880
I did, too.

770
00:37:49,920 --> 00:37:51,200
But it seems impossible now.

771
00:37:52,880 --> 00:37:53,920
Are you lying to yourself?

772
00:37:56,120 --> 00:37:57,280
Maybe you should thank Fan.

773
00:37:57,280 --> 00:37:58,680
He gave you the perfect excuse

774
00:37:58,720 --> 00:38:00,022
to mask your incompetence.

775
00:38:05,840 --> 00:38:06,920
Don't be silly.

776
00:38:08,000 --> 00:38:09,755
The story's father-son relationship

777
00:38:09,880 --> 00:38:11,160
was your main driver.

778
00:38:11,320 --> 00:38:12,777
You don't believe in it anymore,

779
00:38:13,040 --> 00:38:14,160
so you can't write it.

780
00:38:15,080 --> 00:38:16,320
Since the day your father died,

781
00:38:16,320 --> 00:38:17,600
you've been stuck.

782
00:38:20,160 --> 00:38:21,160
In the story, the son

783
00:38:21,444 --> 00:38:22,960
is hunted by his father for miles.

784
00:38:24,120 --> 00:38:25,480
He kills his father to survive.

785
00:38:26,120 --> 00:38:26,840
But in reality,

786
00:38:27,355 --> 00:38:28,800
after your father passed away,

787
00:38:28,800 --> 00:38:29,760
you regretted it.

788
00:38:31,040 --> 00:38:32,280
Regret for not forgiving him.

789
00:38:33,000 --> 00:38:34,880
Regret for holding onto your anger.

790
00:38:35,560 --> 00:38:36,600
You got the story wrong,

791
00:38:37,040 --> 00:38:38,120
but now it's too late.

792
00:38:47,480 --> 00:38:47,880
Yes.

793
00:38:50,640 --> 00:38:52,133
I just can't write it anymore.

794
00:39:01,155 --> 00:39:02,800
It's not just because of him.

795
00:39:04,840 --> 00:39:05,400
It's you,

796
00:39:05,680 --> 00:39:06,280
Lin Zhanqiao.

797
00:39:11,520 --> 00:39:12,000
Because

798
00:39:12,000 --> 00:39:13,520
"Shattered Six States" is our story.

799
00:39:15,044 --> 00:39:16,555
That's why I want to end it.

800
00:39:20,480 --> 00:39:21,720
I think it's time...

801
00:39:30,080 --> 00:39:31,160
But regardless,

802
00:39:34,000 --> 00:39:35,760
I want you to keep writing.

803
00:39:37,400 --> 00:39:38,280
Don't give up.

804
00:39:38,444 --> 00:39:39,733
Give it a proper ending.

805
00:39:44,720 --> 00:39:46,600
Lin Zhanqiao,
aren't you overstepping a bit?

806
00:39:46,840 --> 00:39:48,560
It's just a novel to pay for drinks.

807
00:39:48,560 --> 00:39:49,600
Why take it so seriously?

808
00:39:50,800 --> 00:39:52,800
If one story ends badly, write another.

809
00:39:53,840 --> 00:39:55,720
Since you love studying relationships,

810
00:39:56,640 --> 00:39:58,200
why don't you look at your own parents?

811
00:39:58,920 --> 00:40:00,240
Their relationship is so twisted,

812
00:40:00,240 --> 00:40:01,840
and it would make for a great novel.

813
00:40:01,960 --> 00:40:03,760
Maybe the company would
actually get funded.

814
00:40:03,888 --> 00:40:05,577
Then, you could finally be successful

815
00:40:05,600 --> 00:40:06,760
instead of being stuck

816
00:40:06,920 --> 00:40:07,720
in this wreck,

817
00:40:07,820 --> 00:40:08,920
waiting for it to go bust!

818
00:40:08,920 --> 00:40:10,040
What is wrong with you?

819
00:40:12,320 --> 00:40:14,120
Do you think I like bossing you around?

820
00:40:16,177 --> 00:40:17,933
It serves you right that you're stuck.

821
00:40:18,355 --> 00:40:19,960
You deserve to be called a plagiarist

822
00:40:20,360 --> 00:40:21,680
and have the world turn on you.

823
00:40:22,977 --> 00:40:24,040
Whether you sink or swim,

824
00:40:24,040 --> 00:40:25,280
I'm finished with you.

825
00:40:27,800 --> 00:40:28,920
Whatever novel you write,

826
00:40:28,920 --> 00:40:30,120
I won't give it a second look.

827
00:40:34,640 --> 00:40:35,440
Please don't.

828
00:40:36,440 --> 00:40:37,240
It's an eyesore.

829
00:40:52,170 --> 00:40:54,850
♪I keep asking myself♪

830
00:40:56,680 --> 00:41:00,000
♪What it is I should become♪

831
00:41:01,520 --> 00:41:10,930
♪To follow what my heart truly wants♪

832
00:41:19,420 --> 00:41:22,430
♪Like a drifting dandelion♪

833
00:41:24,220 --> 00:41:27,190
♪Turning where it drifts♪

834
00:41:28,040 --> 00:41:33,130
♪Into soil where it can grow♪

835
00:41:35,020 --> 00:41:38,130
♪When the rain comes, I hide♪

836
00:41:38,810 --> 00:41:41,660
♪In a flower shop at the corner♪

837
00:41:42,470 --> 00:41:48,070
♪Even spring borrows its fragrance♪

838
00:41:52,640 --> 00:41:53,280
A can of beer.

839
00:41:56,940 --> 00:42:03,110
♪Across fields of blooms,
a boat awaits me♪

840
00:42:04,130 --> 00:42:10,750
♪Swaying in the shape of the wind♪

841
00:42:14,200 --> 00:42:15,520
Do you still like her?

842
00:42:18,850 --> 00:42:21,510
♪I want to go on like this♪

843
00:42:21,600 --> 00:42:22,120
Yes.

844
00:42:24,880 --> 00:42:25,760
Very much so.

845
00:42:27,550 --> 00:42:33,850
♪This moment is worth
more than anything♪

846
00:42:34,720 --> 00:42:35,600
(In that moment,)

847
00:42:37,040 --> 00:42:37,880
(both He Han and I)

848
00:42:38,680 --> 00:42:41,040
(had reached our breaking point.)

849
00:42:43,520 --> 00:42:44,480
(Driven by desperation,)

850
00:42:45,720 --> 00:42:48,000
(we lashed out
and hurt each other again.)

851
00:42:50,560 --> 00:42:52,200
(But that wasn't what we intended.)

852
00:42:54,200 --> 00:42:56,240
(We both longed to help each other,)

853
00:42:58,160 --> 00:43:00,120
(but hated how powerless we were.)

854
00:43:05,881 --> 00:43:07,001
(I've been thinking.)

855
00:43:08,281 --> 00:43:11,561
(Everyone's most comfortable level of intimacy)

856
00:43:12,321 --> 00:43:19,651
(is probably different.)

857
00:43:20,651 --> 00:43:22,401
♪If the sky♪

858
00:43:22,911 --> 00:43:24,311
♪And the sea♪

859
00:43:24,851 --> 00:43:26,561
♪Turned upside down♪

860
00:43:28,121 --> 00:43:30,051
♪If a swimming fish♪

861
00:43:30,451 --> 00:43:33,841
♪Fell in love with a flying bird♪

862
00:43:35,611 --> 00:43:37,581
♪If back then♪

863
00:43:37,941 --> 00:43:42,351
♪We had never let go♪

864
00:43:42,951 --> 00:43:49,231
♪We wouldn't be lost in the crowd♪

865
00:43:50,351 --> 00:43:52,501
♪We met in a thirteenth month♪

866
00:43:52,501 --> 00:43:54,371
♪Held each other in a fifth season♪

867
00:43:54,551 --> 00:43:56,991
♪And found our way back whole♪

868
00:43:57,831 --> 00:44:00,001
♪So let this surging love♪

869
00:44:00,001 --> 00:44:04,431
♪Rise like tides that never fall♪

870
00:44:05,331 --> 00:44:07,511
♪If we're caught in a pouring rain♪

871
00:44:07,511 --> 00:44:08,601
♪That's alright♪

872
00:44:09,141 --> 00:44:09,891
♪If we're buried♪

873
00:44:09,891 --> 00:44:12,591
♪By passing years all the better♪

874
00:44:12,851 --> 00:44:15,031
♪At least we still can keep♪

875
00:44:15,211 --> 00:44:19,631
♪This one eternal photograph♪

876
00:44:35,391 --> 00:44:37,681
♪We're on misaligned tracks♪

877
00:44:37,681 --> 00:44:39,441
♪Running in opposite ways♪

878
00:44:39,561 --> 00:44:42,031
♪Searching all along the way♪

879
00:44:42,831 --> 00:44:44,991
♪For the fire of our younger hearts♪

880
00:44:45,181 --> 00:44:50,091
♪And the beauty lost in time♪

881
00:44:50,091 --> 00:44:53,611
♪This time don't lose each other again♪

882
00:44:53,851 --> 00:44:54,821
♪Only after loss♪

883
00:44:54,821 --> 00:44:57,451
♪Do we learn what truly matters most♪

884
00:44:57,861 --> 00:45:00,221
♪In another time and space♪

885
00:45:00,221 --> 00:45:01,781
♪We'll stay and walk together♪

886
00:45:01,781 --> 00:45:04,611
♪Till we grow old♪

887
00:45:05,571 --> 00:45:07,861
♪But still the sky will never♪

888
00:45:07,861 --> 00:45:10,531
♪Turn with the sea♪

889
00:45:13,051 --> 00:45:15,461
♪But still a swimming fish won't♪

890
00:45:15,461 --> 00:45:20,671
♪Fall in love with a flying bird♪
